The paper discusses the issue of users employing too precise topics when searching for documents in digital mathematics libraries, and proposes a solution using navigation between related topics and the count of search results for each topic. This problem and solution are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including information retrieval (cs.IR), digital libraries (cs.DL), computational linguistics (cs.CL), databases (cs.DB), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
